==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|waterfoul}}, {{m|enm|water-foul}}, equivalent to {{com|en|water|fowl}}. Compare {{noncog|ang|dopfugel|t=waterfowl, moorhen|lit=dipping-fowl}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|waterfowl|s}}

# Any of the [[bird]]s, such as [[duck]]s, [[geese]] and [[swan]]s, that spend most of their non-flying time on [[water]]; especially those of the [[family]] [[Anatidae]].

